        <num>CC 807</num>
        <heading>807.  Right to partition; exclusion by agreement</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 807.  Right to partition; exclusion by agreement
No one may be compelled to hold a thing in indivision with another unless the contrary has been provided by law or juridical act.
Any co-owner has a right to demand partition of a thing held in indivision.  Partition may be excluded by agreement for up to fifteen years, or for such other period as provided in R.S. 9:1702 or other specific law.</p>
        </content>
